init_text:
Once upon a time there was an old mother pig who had one hundred little pigs and not enough food to feed them. So when they were old enough, she sent them out into the world to seek their fortunes. You know the story about the first three little pigs. This is a story about the 92nd little pig.

The 92nd little pig built a house out of depleted uranium. And the wolf was like, "dude."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf went to the 91st little pig's house, which was made of straw.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf walked in, ate the pig, and went to sleep.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He was feeling pretty full, so he decided to go to the 92nd little pig's house and eat him.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So he went to the 93rd little pig's house, which was made of wood.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He knocked on the door, and the entire house collapsed, leaving only the door standing.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He walked in, ate the pig, and went to sleep.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I think I'll go to the 94th little pig's house."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He was hungry, and he was angry.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: But then he remembered that the house was made of uranium.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf walked down the street.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf walked up to the front door.
